22 Sec. 16909. (1) The board shall grant a license as a marriage
23 and family therapist to an individual who meets all of the
24 following requirements:
25 (a) Provides satisfactory evidence to the board of meeting
26 either of the following educational qualifications:
27 (i) Has a master's or higher graduate degree from an accredited
28 training program in marriage and family therapy approved by the
29 board.
EMR S01990'25 (S-3) 135a7i

4
1 (ii) Has a master's or higher graduate degree from an
2 accredited college or university approved by the board and has
3 completed all of the following graduate-level courses at an
4 accredited college or university approved by the board:
5 (A) Three courses in family studies that total at least 6
6 semester or 9 quarter hours.
7 (B) Three courses in family therapy methodology that total at
8 least 6 semester or 9 quarter hours.
9 (C) Three courses in human development, personality theory, or
10 psychopathology that total at least 6 semester or 9 quarter hours.
11 (D) At least 2 semester or 3 quarter hours in ethics, law, and
12 standards of professional practice.
13 (E) At least 2 semester or 3 quarter hours in research.
14 (b) Except as otherwise provided in subsection (2), provides
15 satisfactory evidence to the board of having completed supervised
16 clinical marriage and family therapy experience in conjunction with
17 the applicant's educational program. The clinical marriage and
18 family therapy experience described in this subdivision shall must
19 meet all of the following requirements:
20 (i) Be obtained either in a clinical practicum during graduate
21 education or in a postgraduate marriage and family institute
22 training program acceptable to the board.
23 (ii) Be obtained over not less than 8 consecutive months.
24 (iii) Be verified by a supervisor who has a master's or higher
25 graduate degree from an accredited college or university approved
26 by the board and meets 1 of the following:
27 (A) Is a marriage and family therapist.
28 (B) Is a certified licensed master's social worker or a social
29 worker registered under article 16 of the occupational code, 1980
EMR S01990'25 (S-3) 135a7i

5
1 PA 299, MCL 339.1601 to 339.1610.as that term is defined in section
2 18501.
3 (C) Is a licensed professional counselor as that term is
4 defined in section 18101.
5 (D) Is a physician as that term is defined in section 17001 or
6 17501 and practicing in a mental health setting.
7 (E) Is a fully licensed psychologist as that term is defined
8 in section 18201 and is fully licensed.
9 (F) Is an approved supervisor or supervisor-in-training
10 through a program conducted by the American association Association
11 for marriage and family therapy Marriage and Family Therapy and
12 approved by the board.
13 (iv) Include not less than 300 direct client contact hours in
14 supervised clinical marriage and family therapy experience, at
15 least 1/2 of which were completed in a setting in which families,
16 couples, or subsystems of families were physically present in the
17 therapy room.
18 (v) Be supervised in a ratio of at least 1 hour of supervision
19 for each 5 hours of direct client contact, for a total of not less
20 than 60 hours of supervision concurrent with the 300 hours of
21 supervised direct client contact.
22 (c) Except as otherwise provided in subsection (2), provides
23 satisfactory evidence to the board of having completed a minimum of
24 1,000 direct client contact hours in supervised marriage and family
25 therapy experience, at least 1/2 of which was completed with
26 families, couples, or subsystems of families physically present in
27 the therapy room, that meets all of the following conditions:
28 (i) Is verified by the supervising licensed marriage and family
29 therapist.
EMR S01990'25 (S-3) 135a7i

6
1 (ii) Is obtained following the completion of the degree
2 required by subdivision (a)(i), is obtained following the completion
3 of the degree required by subdivision (a)(ii) and concurrent with or
4 following the course work specified in subdivision (a)(ii)(A), (B),
5 (C), (D), and (E), or is obtained as part of a doctoral program in
6 marriage and family therapy from an accredited college or
7 university approved by the board, which experience may include
8 experience obtained under subdivision (b)(i).
9 (iii) Is supervised in a ratio of at least 1 hour of supervision
10 for each 5 hours of experience, for a total of not less than 200
11 hours of supervision concurrent with the 1,000 hours of supervised
12 experience. Not less than 100 hours of supervision under this
13 subparagraph shall must be individual supervision with no more than
14 1 other supervisee present. The remaining supervision under this
15 subparagraph may be group supervision involving no more than 6
16 supervisees with 1 supervisor. The supervision shall must be given
17 in face-to-face contact with the individual obtaining marriage and
18 family therapy experience.
19 (2) The board shall waive the requirements of subsection
20 (1)(b) and (c) for an applicant who provides satisfactory evidence
21 to the board of having obtained a doctoral degree from an
22 accredited doctoral training program in marriage and family therapy
23 approved by the board.
24 (3) This section is repealed effective January 1, 2028.
25 Sec. 16909a. (1) Beginning January 1, 2028, subject to this
26 section, to be granted a license as a marriage and family
27 therapist, an individual must meet all of the following
28 requirements:
29 (a) The individual provides satisfactory evidence to the
EMR S01990'25 (S-3) 135a7i

7
1 department that the individual holds a master's or higher graduate
2 degree from an accredited training program in marriage and family
3 therapy approved by the board, the Commission on Accreditation for
4 Marriage and Family Therapy Education, or a regionally accredited
5 body. The department, in consultation with the board, shall
6 promulgate rules establishing standards to approve programs under
7 this subdivision.
8 (b) The individual provides satisfactory evidence to the
9 department of having completed supervised clinical marriage and
10 family therapy experience in conjunction with the individual's
11 educational program.
12 (c) The individual provides satisfactory evidence to the
13 department of having completed 3,000 hours of supervised postdegree
14 clinical marriage and family therapy experience in not less than 24
15 months, at least 500 hours of which were completed in a setting in
16 which families, couples, or subsystems of families were present in
17 the same location or a setting in which families, couples, or
18 subsystems of families met by way of 2-way real-time secure
19 technology that allowed direct, contemporaneous interaction by
20 sight or sound. The supervision required under this subdivision
21 must include not less than 100 hours of supervision by a supervisor
22 with not less than 50 of those 100 hours consisting of either
23 individual supervision or dyadic supervision with no more than 1
24 other supervisee present. The remaining 50 of the 100 hours of
25 supervision required under this subdivision may be group
26 supervision involving no more than 6 supervisees with 1 supervisor.
27 The 100 hours of supervision described in this subdivision must be
28 in person or use 2-way real-time secure technology with the
29 individual obtaining the supervised clinical marriage and family
EMR S01990'25 (S-3) 135a7i

8
1 therapy experience. To qualify as a supervisor under this
2 subdivision, an individual must meet the requirements described in
3 subsection (4). The department, in consultation with the board, may
4 promulgate rules to do the following:
5 (i) Revise the number of supervised clinical hours required
6 under this subdivision if necessary to ensure a marriage and family
7 therapist's eligibility to enroll as a provider with Medicare.
8 (ii) Supplement the requirements for supervisors under this
9 subdivision, including, but not limited to, by requiring additional
10 professional experience or the completion of continuing education.
11 (2) The board shall waive the requirements of subsection
12 (1)(b) and (c) for an applicant who provides satisfactory evidence
13 to the board of having obtained a doctoral degree from an
14 accredited doctoral training program in marriage and family therapy
15 approved by the board.
16 (3) The department, in consultation with the board, may
17 promulgate rules to supplement the requirements for licensure under
18 this part as a marriage and family therapist as the department
19 determines is necessary to adapt to changes in federal law or
20 national industry standards for marriage and family therapists.
21 (4) To qualify as a supervisor under subsection (1)(c), an
22 individual must be 1 of the following:
23 (a) A marriage and family therapist.
24 (b) An individual who meets both of the following
25 requirements:
26 (i) The individual is 1 of the following:
27 (A) A licensed master's social worker as that term is defined
28 in section 18501.
29 (B) A licensed professional counselor as that term is defined
EMR S01990'25 (S-3) 135a7i

9
1 in section 18101.
2 (C) A psychologist as that term is defined in section 18201
3 who is fully licensed.
4 (ii) The individual is an approved supervisor through a program
5 conducted by the American Association for Marriage and Family
6 Therapy and approved by the board.
7 (5) As used in this section, "Medicare" means that term as
8 defined in section 2701.
9 Sec. 16914. (1) Notwithstanding the requirements of part 161,
10 the department, in consultation with the board, shall promulgate
11 rules requiring a licensee seeking renewal of a license to furnish
12 the department with satisfactory evidence that, during the license
13 cycle immediately preceding the application for renewal, the
14 licensee has attended continuing education courses or programs
15 approved by the board in subjects related to the practice of
16 marriage and family therapy and designed to further educate
17 licensees.
18 (2) As required under section 16204, the department, in
19 consultation with the board, shall promulgate rules requiring each
20 applicant for license renewal to complete as part of the
21 educational courses or programs required under subsection (1) an
22 appropriate number of hours or courses in pain and symptom
23 management.
24 (3) The continuing education requirements of this section
25 apply beginning with the first renewal cycle after January 1, 2028.
